133
00:11:56,048 --> 00:11:58,259
I'm sure they'll arrest him soon,

134
00:11:58,342 --> 00:12:00,094
but still, be careful.

135
00:12:01,387 --> 00:12:03,139
I have you with me.

136
00:12:04,807 --> 00:12:07,893
I'm not afraid of anything
when I have you next to me.

137
00:12:11,397 --> 00:12:14,984
Also, thank you for saving me earlier.

138
00:12:18,237 --> 00:12:20,865
You punk. I'm not your bodyguard.

139
00:12:20,948 --> 00:12:23,200
Don't ruin the mood, will you?

140
00:12:27,121 --> 00:12:28,456
You'll be at school

141
00:12:28,539 --> 00:12:30,624
when the new semester begins, right?

142
00:12:34,920 --> 00:12:36,130
Right?

143
00:12:36,672 --> 00:12:39,842
Of course, you punk!
I have nowhere to go anyway.

144
00:12:41,969 --> 00:12:42,970
I'll see you next semester then.

145
00:12:50,186 --> 00:12:51,395
Wait!

146
00:12:56,567 --> 00:12:57,902
We wouldn't have been able

147
00:12:58,402 --> 00:12:59,987
to arrest him without you today.

148
00:13:02,573 --> 00:13:04,492
I'm saying
it's all thanks to you, partner.

149
00:13:07,244 --> 00:13:08,329
Also,

150
00:13:09,246 --> 00:13:14,126
I'm ecstatic that I caught that jerk.

151
00:13:27,056 --> 00:13:29,892
SEOUL METROPOLITAN POLICE AGENCY

152
00:13:29,975 --> 00:13:31,352
Are you here
because of the illegal gambling ring?

153
00:13:31,435 --> 00:13:33,020
-What did they say?
-Nothing much.

154
00:13:33,103 --> 00:13:34,480
What about you? Any good news?

155
00:13:35,105 --> 00:13:35,981
Excuse me.

156
00:13:37,858 --> 00:13:39,818
-Dong-man!
-Gosh.

157
00:13:39,902 --> 00:13:43,280
I decided to serve you
as my big brother from today.

158
00:13:43,364 --> 00:13:45,908
You're a true detective, not a pig.

159
00:13:45,991 --> 00:13:48,160
And you're super loyal.

160
00:13:48,244 --> 00:13:49,245
Jeez, stop it.

161
00:13:49,828 --> 00:13:51,747
Just write up good articles.

162
00:13:51,830 --> 00:13:55,251
Don't just write click-baits, got it?

163
00:13:56,001 --> 00:13:57,378
You can trust me.

164
00:13:57,461 --> 00:14:00,256
I'll repay you with my article
since you called me the first thing.

165
00:14:01,090 --> 00:14:05,052
By the way, have you not identified
the suspect who fled from the scene?

166
00:14:08,222 --> 00:14:10,933
His name is Jang Jae-gyu,
and he is 30 years old.

167
00:14:11,016 --> 00:14:12,893
His records are shown below.

168
00:14:12,977 --> 00:14:14,687
He was convicted five times of fraud

169
00:14:14,770 --> 00:14:17,189
and twice of attempted murder and assault.

170
00:14:18,232 --> 00:14:21,694
Gosh, this bastard is such a mess.

171
00:14:21,777 --> 00:14:24,446
It took some time to find out
about his residence.

172
00:14:24,530 --> 00:14:26,532
We'll be asking around from today.

173
00:14:27,616 --> 00:14:28,784
Okay.

174
00:14:28,868 --> 00:14:30,160
Right, Dong-man.

175
00:14:30,786 --> 00:14:32,830
In the witness statement,

176
00:14:32,913 --> 00:14:35,749
you wrote that you saw him
talking on the phone

177
00:14:35,833 --> 00:14:36,917
while coming out.

178
00:14:37,793 --> 00:14:38,961
Yes, what about it?

179
00:14:39,044 --> 00:14:42,131
We've received the seized evidence
from the KCSI.

180
00:14:42,631 --> 00:14:45,926
I've searched through them,
but there were no phones.

181
00:14:47,219 --> 00:14:48,345
What?

182
00:14:53,684 --> 00:14:54,977
We're done, right?

183
00:14:56,228 --> 00:14:59,148
Well, you've confessed to everything,

184
00:14:59,231 --> 00:15:00,774
and we've got solid evidence.

185
00:15:05,821 --> 00:15:09,533
But there's one thing
I really want to ask you, Mr. Go.

186
00:15:10,826 --> 00:15:14,830
I've checked the transactions
of your illegal gambling ring.

187
00:15:14,914 --> 00:15:18,042
Every month for six years,

188
00:15:18,125 --> 00:15:20,878
you've consistently cashed out
the money at ATMs.

189
00:15:20,961 --> 00:15:23,047
Always 80 percent of your revenue.

190
00:15:25,382 --> 00:15:28,010
I'm sure you didn't just save them
somewhere else.

191
00:15:30,930 --> 00:15:32,723
What did you do with all that money?

192
00:15:35,517 --> 00:15:38,354
What do you think?
I've put it to good use.

193
00:15:43,442 --> 00:15:44,985
Where's your phone?

194
00:15:48,864 --> 00:15:51,992
I saw you talking on the phone,

195
00:15:52,576 --> 00:15:55,037
so don't try to play tricks on me
and tell me.

196
00:15:55,120 --> 00:15:56,664
What did you do with it, you punk?

197
00:15:58,082 --> 00:15:59,333
What phone?

198
00:16:00,918 --> 00:16:03,462
Stop saying nonsense, Professor Yu.

199
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:09,802
You've made your confession,

200
00:16:09,885 --> 00:16:12,012
but you're going to play dumb about this?

201
00:16:17,893 --> 00:16:19,812
There's something in that phone, right?

202
00:16:28,487 --> 00:16:31,031
You're not in charge of this case.

203
00:16:32,366 --> 00:16:34,868
Do I need to answer his questions,
Captain Choi?

204
00:16:36,328 --> 00:16:38,330
